[normal]Author presented the application of the Bayesian method of statistics (i.e. rules of conditional probabilities) to
[normal] determine the quantitative reliability of train driver (human performance) in 
[normal]dangerous situations in 
[normal]the form of a poster session at the IET System Safety Conference in 2010. Author had used 
[normal]simplified
[normal] 
[normal]Bayesian method of statistics
[normal] in his submission to t
[normal]he UK Law Commission Inquiry on Level Crossings(Appicharla, 2010). Author noted that Bayesian
[normal] method can be
[normal] applied where errors in statistical risk analysis are to be identified as suggested by Nobel Laureate Daniel Kahneman
[normal]. This is
[normal] to overcome the biase
[normal]s inherent in
[normal] risk perceptions by public and experts as well. 
[normal]Author 
[normal]explained 
[normal]this in a general way 
[normal]in the Technical Review of the Common Safety Method presented at the IET System Safety Conference in October 2013
[normal] 
[normal]and in the Submission to the UK Law Commi
[normal]ssion in 2010 (Appicharla, 2010),
[normal](Appicharla, 2013)
[normal]. 
